column6: It has found a steady band to currently trade in
Late prediction, but has stabilized over the past week. THB increasing on EUR, but EUR decreasing against USD.
What is to change the direction?
I tried a couple forecast methods and they both suggested that this is going to keep tracking down for the immediate future.
The Baht has been rising next to the dollar for quite some time. At this time USD is falling in relation to most major (and minor) currency pairs.

Trading economics (https://tradingeconomics.com/thailand/currency/forecast) seem higher than the FRED looks where it is heading but then the forecasts are old. Consensus here seems low. So heavily weighted to our consensus but dragged a little higher.
It is at 3 cents to one Baht today.
